Medication: Wellbutrin, Fluoxetine, and Prilosec daily.

Complaint: 2 days of strange dull/sharp ache on behind right ear. Started suddenly and last night after a few hours it spread to behind my left ear as well. It throbs and is tender to touch.
  I have a history of migraines but they are typically above my eyes. This is an entirely new type of pain. It started while I was wearing my reading glasses Friday evening. If you’re familiar with that pain that comes from wearing glasses for a long time, that’s kind of what it feels like but more intense. I haven’t worn them since.
